                <dc:description xml:lang="en">Tapestry with the Covenant of God and Noah. With the arms of Margaret of Parma, regent of the Netherlands. From a series with the history of Noah. Wool and silk. Brussels, ca. 1565, by Willem de Pannemaker, the design attributed to Michiel Coxcie. Gift of the Committee for Photographic Sales, 1955.</dc:description>
